.SH "NAME"
fromman \- show description, help, repository, version or subsections (SYNOPSYS, etc.) from man page
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
\fBfromman\fP [\fICOMMAND|PATH\fP] [\fIOPTION\fP] ...
Unresolved directive in fromman.adoc \- include::/usr/local/include/man/SYNOPSIS\-ARGUMENTS_Information.adoc[]
.fi
.br
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fBfromman\fP command will show information from man page of \fICOMMAND|PATH\fP (default: \fBfromman\fP),
if the first \fIOPTION\fP (\fI$1\fP \fBfromman\fP and \fI$2\fP for others) is an option in the \fI[_arguments\-information]\fP list.
The program will return \fI1\fP, if there is a match in \fIOPTION\fP (\fI$2\fP), to indicate the caller to exit.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB[COMMAND|PATH]\fP
.RS 4
\fIPATH\fP to get name of command from basename or \fICOMMAND\fP.
.RE
.sp
Unresolved directive in fromman.adoc \- include::/usr/local/include/man/ARGUMENTS\-Information.adoc[]
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.sp
\fB0\fP
.RS 4
When called directly (\fI$SHLVL=2\fP) and an argument from:_[_arguments\-information]_
found in \fIOPTION\fP (\fI$2\fP) with value from man page.
.RE
.sp
\fB1\fP
.RS 4
Program will return \fI1\fP for the following conditions:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
